This paper is about evaluating generative models, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on using a classifier trained with generated data to assess the quality of a generative model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments are conducted on image datasets. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper discusses the potential of generative models to help discriminative neural networks learn.
